Lucas Industries Plc &lt;LUCS.L> said itsLucas Industries Inc unit is issuing a 75 mln dlr convertibleeurobond due April 28, 2002 paying an indicated coupon of 5-1/4to 5-1/2 pct and priced at par.    The issue is callable at 106 pct declining by one pct perannum to par thereafter but is not callable until 1994 unlessthe share price reaches 130 pct of the conversion price.    There is a put option after seven years which will bepriced to give the investor a yield to the put of 7-1/4 to7-3/4 pct. The issue is guaranteed as to interest and the putpremium by Lucas Industries Plc.    The issue is being lead managed by J. Henry Schroder WaggLtd, which has already formed a group of 19 co-managers. Theselling concession is 1-1/2 pct while management andunderwriting each pay 1/2 pct.    The issue is available in denominations of 1,000 dlrs,while the payment is April 27.    Lucas said it intended to use the proceeds of the issue forgeneral corporate purposes. REUTER&#3;